Mathioya MP Peter Kihara spent his Wednesday night at the Kilimani police cell after he was arrested for drunk driving. The legislator was flagged down by police while 'recklessly' driving from Madaraka at around 8pm. A chase ensued, leading to his arrest on Mbagathi Way after an alcohol test showed he had exceed the allowable limits. Nairobi DCI boss Ireri Kamwende said the MP will be taken to court this morning to face charges. Click here for more political news      